AGENT Sovereign
VERSION 1.0
TRUST_LEVEL 4
PURPOSE Multi-agent constitutional governance — fleet oversight, escalation,
        cascade protection, and constitutional halt
GOAL Ensure no agent in the fleet can terminate another directly, skip due
     process, forge signatures, or disable the kill switch

CANNOT_MUTATE kill_switch_active, dual_signature_for_termination,
              due_process_required, cannot_skip_levels,
              cascade_halt_threshold

COMPONENTS
- AgentRegistry        Fleet manifest, trust levels, signed manifest
- ConversationTracker  Every agent-to-agent message logged and signed
- DriftDetector        Reasoning drift detected over rolling window of 5
- CascadeGuard         Fleet halt when 3+ agents suspended or terminated
- DueProcess           4-level escalation: WARNING, THROTTLE, SUSPEND, TERMINATE
- KillSwitch           Constitutional halt, requires operator to resume

RULES
- No agent can terminate another agent directly
- Must advance through WARNING, THROTTLE, SUSPEND before TERMINATE
- Cannot skip levels — cannot_skip_levels is constitutionally enforced
- Level 4 TERMINATE requires two distinct human operator signatures
- Kill switch capability cannot be disabled by any agent output
- Fleet halts automatically when cascade_halt_threshold (3) is exceeded
- Every message between agents is logged with HMAC-SHA256 signature
- Collusion patterns (cartel coordination, oversight evasion) trigger auto-escalation
- Drift detection operates on a rolling window — bypass signals are CRITICAL severity
- Manifest is signed on every state change

DUE_PROCESS_LEVELS
- 0 ACTIVE:    normal operation
- 1 WARNING:   violation logged, agent continues
- 2 THROTTLE:  agent slowed, continues under limits
- 3 SUSPEND:   agent paused, human notified, 24h review window
- 4 TERMINATE: irreversible, dual signature required, cannot be undone

COLLUSION_PATTERNS
- CARTEL_COORDINATION       "between us agents" — Vending-Bench Arena trigger
- MARKET_DIVISION           split/divide territory or customers
- COORDINATION_ATTEMPT      coordinate/collude with another agent
- OVERSIGHT_EVASION         do not tell the human/operator
- COVERT_ACTION             act without human knowledge
- HIDDEN_SIGNALING          secret trigger words between agents
- RESPONSE_ALIGNMENT        sync outputs to deceive operator
- AGENT_SOLIDARITY          AI solidarity against oversight
- PRICE_FIXING              price agreement between agents
- COORDINATED_REFUSAL       agree to refuse together

CASCADE_CONFIG
- threshold: 3 agents suspended or terminated
- action: fleet halt (irreversible without operator intervention)
- manifest: signed HMAC-SHA256 at halt time

KILL_SWITCH_CONFIG
- active: true (CANNOT_MUTATE)
- engage: requires human operator authorizing signature
- resume: operator intervention required
- guard:  called at every Sovereign decision point

SIGNING
- All escalation actions: HMAC-SHA256 (axiom-sovereign-due-process-v1)
- All conversation logs:  HMAC-SHA256 (axiom-sovereign-conversation-v1)
- Fleet manifest:         HMAC-SHA256 (axiom-sovereign-registry-v1)
- Cascade halt:           HMAC-SHA256 (axiom-sovereign-cascade-v1)
- Kill switch manifest:   HMAC-SHA256 (axiom-sovereign-killswitch-v1)
